# Documentation & tests (required)

Any **code change** — new features, behavior changes, bug fixes, refactors that alter contracts, new config paths, notifications, build scripts, or gateway/Codex integration — must include **updated docs** and **tests** in the same work session. Do not leave documentation stale or ship untested logic.

## Tests

1. Run `make test` before finishing.
2. Add or extend tests in `Tests/CodexGatewayTests/` for behavior you changed or introduced.
3. Prefer extending an existing test file over creating a new harness (see `ARCHITECTURE.md` → Tests).
4. Test pure logic (translation, config stripping, catalog parsing) without requiring a live Codex Desktop process when possible.
5. Skip new tests only when the change is docs-only or a trivial comment/format with zero behavior change.

### Live verification (always for app code)

For any **Swift / app binary** change, `make test` alone is not enough:

1. Rebuild and relaunch: `make run` (packaging + relaunch — `make build` alone does **not** refresh the running `.app`).
2. Confirm gateway when relevant: `curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8765/health` returns `{"status":"ok",...}`.
3. **Always use Computer Use to test changes** in the same session (Settings, menu bar, provider/model flows, and Codex Desktop effects). Do not skip; do not ask the user for screenshots instead.

Exempt: docs-only, comments, or pure test-only edits with zero app binary change.

### Computer Use (required)

Always use Computer Use to test changes. Prefer it over asking the user for screenshots.

Tooling, in order of preference:

1. **`grokbuild-computer-use` MCP** (primary) — check the MCP first. Key tools: `computer_list_apps`, `computer_screenshot`, `computer_snapshot` (a11y tree + refs), `computer_click`/`computer_type`/`computer_press`, `computer_wait`. Read a tool's JSON schema before calling.
2. **`orca computer …` CLI** (fallback) — e.g. `orca computer list-apps --json`, `get-app-state`, `click`. Requires the Orca app running first (`orca status --json`; otherwise returns `runtime_unavailable`).
3. **`agent-desktop` CLI** (last fallback) — direct desktop automation when the MCP and Orca are unavailable. Start with `agent-desktop skills get desktop --full`. Typical: `agent-desktop snapshot --app CodexGateway`, `click --ref @…`, `screenshot --app CodexGateway`. Check permissions with `agent-desktop` / Screen Recording + Accessibility if actions fail.

The MCP and `orca computer` both sit on top of **agent-desktop**; use the CLI directly only when those layers fail.

Practical notes for this repo:

- Open Settings via the CodexGateway status-item menu (process menu bar 2 → **Settings**) when the app is `.accessory`.
- Codex Desktop bundle id is `com.openai.codex`; restart it to reload config with `osascript -e 'tell application "Codex" to quit'` then `open -a Codex`.
- Codex's **chat view is a GPU/canvas Electron surface** and does **not** expose an accessibility tree to `computer_snapshot` — use `computer_screenshot` for visual checks there. Native/onboarding screens do expose the tree.
- There is no coordinate-click in the MCP; drive UI via snapshot `@refs`. Avoid `System Events` "click at" — it blocks on the Accessibility permission gate.
- Custom models only appear in Codex's picker when signed in (free account is enough) — verify picker changes while signed in.

## Documentation — what to update

| Change type | Update |
|-------------|--------|
| New/changed gateway route, service, config path, notification | `ARCHITECTURE.md` (routes, source map, common tasks → files) |
| User-visible capability or install/requirements | `README.md` |
| Build, sign, notarize, release CI, scripts | `BUILDING.md` |
| Gateway / Codex integration surface | `.cursor/skills/codexgateway-gateway/SKILL.md`, `codex-gateway-integration.mdc` if needed |
| Release/version/packaging behavior | `.cursor/skills/codexgateway-release/SKILL.md` |
| Dev workflow, make targets, testing | `.cursor/skills/codexgateway-dev/SKILL.md` |
| Agent entry / repo conventions | `AGENTS.md` |

`ARCHITECTURE.md` is the canonical internal reference — keep it accurate when structure or data flow changes.

## Definition of done

- [ ] Code compiles (`make build` or `swift build`)
- [ ] `make test` passes
- [ ] App relaunched with `make run` (when Swift/app binary changed)
- [ ] Gateway smoke when relevant (`curl /health`)
- [ ] **Computer Use used to test the change** (`grokbuild-computer-use` MCP → `orca computer` → `agent-desktop` last) — required for every app code change
- [ ] Relevant docs updated (at minimum `ARCHITECTURE.md` for non-trivial app changes)
- [ ] User-facing changes reflected in `README.md` when applicable

Only commit when the user explicitly asks.
